	parameter of the system or a dynamical variable. Chaos control usually
	involves two steps. In the first, unstable periodic orbits (UPOs)
	that are embedded in the chaotic set are identified. After that,
	a control technique is employed in order to stabilize a desirable
	orbit. This contribution employs the close-return method to identify
	UPOs and a semi-continuous control method, which is built up on the
